# ANTLR4 Grammar for NMODL

## Overview

[NMODL](https://www.neuron.yale.edu/neuron/static/docs/help/neuron/nmodl/nmodl.html) (NEURON Model Description Language) is a domain-specific language used to define models for the [NEURON simulator](http://neuron.yale.edu/neuron/). This ANTLR4 grammar provides a formal specification for parsing NMODL code, enabling syntax highlighting, code analysis, and other tooling for developers working with NEURON.


## Installation

To use the NMODL grammar with ANTLR4, follow these steps:

1. **Install ANTLR4**: Ensure you have ANTLR4 installed. You can download it from [ANTLR's official website](https://www.antlr.org/download.html).

2. **Clone the Repository**: Clone the repository containing the NMODL grammar files.

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/antlr/grammars-v4.git
   cd nmodl
   ```

3. **Generate the Parser**: Use ANTLR4 to generate the parser and lexer from the grammar file.

   ```
   antlr4 nmodl.g4
   ```

4. **Test**: Use MVN to test .mod files in `/examples` directory.

   ```
   mvn clean test
   ```

5. **Integrate with Your Project**: Include the generated files in your project and set up your build system to use them.

## Usage

Once integrated, you can use the generated parser to parse NMODL files. Hereâ€™s a simple example of how to use the parser in JavaScript:

```
import antlr4 from 'antlr4';
import NmodlLexer from './NmodlLexer.js';
import NmodlParser from './NmodlParser.js';

const input = "NEURON { ... }"; // Your NMODL code here
const chars = new antlr4.InputStream(input);
const lexer = new NmodlLexer(chars);
const tokens = new antlr4.CommonTokenStream(lexer);
const parser = new NmodlParser(tokens);

const tree = parser.startRule(); // Replace with the appropriate start rule
console.log(tree.toStringTree(parser.ruleNames));
```

